frontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:1020:                    <span className=\"workspace-stage-detail__route\">\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:1041:              <section className=\"workspace-stage-panel\">\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:1053:                  description=\"Saved notes become durable session context, show up in replayable history, and feed the backend agent summary.\"\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:1057:                  onChange={(event) => {\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:1058:                    setStageNoteDraft(event.currentTarget.value)\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:1101:              <section className=\"workspace-stage-detail__list\">\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:1123:            className=\"workspace-overview-grid\"\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:1128:                hint={`Resume at ${getWorkflowStageLabel(snapshot.resume_stage)} with ${progress.percent}% of the workflow currently complete.`}\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:23:        |         +--> repositories for sessions, workflow state, jobs, and event log\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:40:The frontend should only call the backend's API and subscribe to backend-owned progress events.\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:49:- retries, cancellation, and resume logic need explicit job state rather than transient in-memory state\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:51:The durable model should include job records, segment records, asset metadata, and an event log that can reconstruct session progress after interruption.\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:61:- `repositories/`: database access for sessions, events, jobs, and assets\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:4:before any model suggestion is allowed to touch the workspace.\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:40:| `composition` | `start_composition`, `pause_job`, `resume_job`, `redirect_composition`           | Job control is explicit and stage-bound. Redirects require concrete instructions.                     |\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:41:| `audio`       | `update_audio_settings`, `start_audio_generation`, `pause_job`, `resume_job`     | Audio settings are separate from the command to start generation.                                     |\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:3:This document defines the append-only event contract introduced in prompt 15.\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:4:The goal is to make session history durable enough for replay, resume debugging,\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:9:- Every event belongs to exactly one `story_session`.\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:11:- Events always record an actor, a stable `event_type`, a human-readable `summary`,\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:17:  - `system`: worker-owned or infrastructure-owned progress events.\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:22:The backend centralizes these names in `backend/app/models/events.py` as `SessionEventType`.\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:23:New event types should be added there before they are emitted anywhere else.\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:33:| `ui.action.recorded` | Direct UI interactions that should survive refresh and replay. | `user` | optional |\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:34:| `composition.progress.recorded` | Durable composition job progress for replay and worker debugging. | `system` | `composition` |\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:35:| `audio.progress.recorded` | Durable narration job progress for replay and worker debugging. | `system` | `audio` |\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:39:Known event types use typed Pydantic payload models in `backend/app/models/events.py`.\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:59:  \"resume_stage\": \"pitches\",\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:70:  \"source\": \"workspace\",\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:75:  \"summary_text\": \"Updated beat sheet notes from the workspace.\"\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:79:For one-off service-owned events that do not yet deserve a first-class payload class,\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:80:`SessionEventLogService.append_event(...)` still injects `schema_version: 1`\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:85:The primary append/read surface is `backend/app/services/event_log.py`.\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:98:- `append_event(...)` for lower-level extension points\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:102:`backend/app/repositories/events.py`. It is responsible for per-session sequencing and\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:108:Record a selection event:\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:112:from app.services.event_log import SessionEventLogService\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:114:event_log = SessionEventLogService(db_session)\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:115:event_log.record_selection(\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:128:event_log.record_composition_progress(\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:141:history = event_log.list_session_history(session_id, after_sequence_number=10)\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:142:for event in history.events:\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:143:    print(event.sequence_number, event.event_type, event.summary)\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:152:  `summary_text` so later prompts, summaries, and chat replay can stay grounded\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:153:  without re-reading the entire raw event stream.\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:154:- Do not rewrite or delete historical events to \"fix\" history. Emit a new compensating event.\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:155:- When a workflow-stage event changes the truth seen by the UI, attach the emitted event\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:156:  back to affected `workflow_stage_states.last_event_id` so snapshots can explain why a stage looks the way it does.\ndocs/system-diagram.md:3:This diagram shows the intended runtime shape for Storyteller after the core session, worker, and realtime prompts are built. It documents where session resume, durable event history, realtime delivery, and long-running jobs belong.\ndocs/system-diagram.md:9:    WS[\"WebSocket session stream<br/>replay recent events + deliver live progress\"]\ndocs/system-diagram.md:11:    Postgres[(\"PostgreSQL<br/>sessions, workflow state,<br/>durable event history,<br/>job records, asset metadata\")]\ndocs/system-diagram.md:16:    API -->|\"resume session snapshot\"| Browser\ndocs/system-diagram.md:20:    WS -->|\"replay recent events and current job state\"| Postgres\ndocs/system-diagram.md:23:    Worker -->|\"claim jobs, persist partial outputs,<br/>append durable events\"| Postgres\ndocs/system-diagram.md:35:- Resume starts from PostgreSQL session state plus durable event history.\ndocs/frontend-state-architecture.md:14:   - This tracks pending UI actions and the buffered live-event stream without\ndocs/frontend-state-architecture.md:25:- The local runtime store keeps websocket/event-stream concerns separate from\ndocs/frontend-state-architecture.md:28:  mutating or duplicating the session snapshot shape.\ndocs/frontend-state-architecture.md:50:const eventStream = useSessionEventStream()\ndocs/frontend-state-architecture.md:67:When the server later emits a matching live event, `appendLiveEvent()` can mark\ndocs/secrets-and-local-config.md:41:The Docker Compose backend service mounts the repository at `/workspace` and sets:\ndocs/secrets-and-local-config.md:44:STORYTELLER_SECRETS_FILE=/workspace/secrets.yaml\ndocs/chat-action-echoes.md:4:workspace interactions and chat-driven UI changes without turning the left pane\ndocs/chat-action-echoes.md:5:into a noisy event dump.\ndocs/chat-action-echoes.md:20:  yet durably applied by the current workspace surface.\ndocs/chat-action-echoes.md:23:    durable `ui.action.recorded` event\ndocs/chat-action-echoes.md:36:- Durable replay comes from `GET /api/v1/sessions/{session_id}/history`.\ndocs/chat-action-echoes.md:37:- Direct workspace clicks persist through `POST /api/v1/sessions/{session_id}/ui-actions`.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:15:- chat and direct UI actions both need an audit trail that can be replayed during resume\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:33:PostgreSQL owns the structured state required to resume a story session.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:39:- durable event history\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:49:Session resume should come from durable state, not browser cache. The event history is part of the product, not just an internal log, because it supports replay, auditability, and UI-to-chat echoes.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:66:- WebSockets handle session progress, job status, and incremental event delivery.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:67:- On reconnect, the client should rehydrate from durable session state and recent event history before continuing with live updates.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:76:- Workers claim pending jobs, call Gemini or narration providers, persist partial outputs, and append durable events.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:79:This separation keeps request latency predictable and makes pause, resume, retry, and interruption logic easier to reason about.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:96:- Resume and replay have a clear home in durable data.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:105:- Developers need to think about job state transitions and event ordering early.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:110:- Treat the durable event history as product data that can be queried during session resume.\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:5:    \"session_event\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:87:            \"event_id\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:92:            \"event_log_entry_id\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:100:            \"replayable\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:143:            \"event_id\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:147:            \"event_log_entry_id\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:304:            \"event_id\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:309:            \"event_log_entry_id\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:317:            \"replayable\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:355:            \"event_id\",\ndo