           \"event_log_entry_id\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1563:            \"hydrate\"\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1633:        \"replay_from_sequence_number\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1646:        \"replay_strategy\": {\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:16:    \"resume_job\": \"confirm_first\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:932:              \"const\": \"resume_job\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:933:              \"default\": \"resume_job\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:2010:          \"resume_job\": \"#/$defs/ResumeJobAction\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:2993:              \"const\": \"resume_job\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:2994:              \"default\": \"resume_job\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:4075:                \"resume_job\": \"#/$defs/ResumeJobAction\",\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:12:  resume_stage: 'beats',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:149:  events: [\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:151:      id: 'event-1',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:158:      event_type: 'session.created',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:168:      id: 'event-2',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:175:      event_type: 'selection.recorded',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:188:      id: 'event-3',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:195:      event_type: 'selection.recorded',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:208:      id: 'event-4',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:215:      event_type: 'chat.message.recorded',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:253:    id: `ui-event-${String(body.action ?? 'unknown')}`,\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:260:    event_type: 'ui.action.recorded',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:268:      origin: body.origin ?? 'workspace',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:292:              last_event_summary:\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:293:                'Updated beat sheet notes from the workspace.',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:294:              last_event_type: 'content.user_edit.recorded',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:295:              last_event_at: '2026-04-01T03:05:00Z',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:301:    event: {\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:302:      id: 'context-update-event',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:309:      event_type: 'content.user_edit.recorded',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:316:        source: body.origin ?? 'workspace',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:321:        summary_text: 'Updated beat sheet notes from the workspace.',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:378:        ? 'I can move the workspace to Story setup.'\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:379:        : 'I can translate that command into the story workspace.',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:545:  it('renders the session snapshot inside the workspace shell', async () => {\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:556:    expect(screen.getByTestId('workspace-route')).toBeInTheDocument()\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:733:      await screen.findByText('I can move the workspace to Story setup.'),\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:775:      await screen.findByText('Updated beat sheet notes from the workspace.'),\ndocs/domain-model.md:3:This document defines the durable business objects and workflow rules for a single story-creation session. The goal is to give the backend, frontend, migrations, and later AI orchestration code one shared contract for how a session progresses, pauses, rewinds, and resumes.\ndocs/domain-model.md:16:The session snapshot returned to the UI should eventually include these fields, even if some land in later prompts:\ndocs/domain-model.md:23:| `resume_stage` | Earliest stage that still needs work when a session is reopened. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:38:`resume_stage` is the key anti-guessing field. The backend computes it from durable stage states so the frontend does not need to infer where to reopen a session by looking at which panels happen to have data.\ndocs/domain-model.md:50:| `workflow_stage_state` | Per-stage state for the session. | `session_id`, `stage`, `status`, `updated_at`, `last_event_id`. | Stored explicitly so resume does not depend on sparse child tables. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:62:| `event_log_entry` | Append-only session history. | actor, event type, stage context, payload with `schema_version`, created_at. | Supports replay, resume hydration, debugging, and audit. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:121:- If all stages are `completed`, `resume_stage` is `finalize`.\ndocs/domain-model.md:123:This is the behavior implemented by the `resolve_resume_stage` helper in both the backend and frontend contract files.\ndocs/domain-model.md:151:- A composition job may move between `in_progress`, paused, resumed, or cancelled states without leaving the `composition` stage.\ndocs/domain-model.md:164:   - Result: open the session on `resume_stage = pitches`.\ndocs/domain-model.md:167:   - Result: `composition`, `audio`, and `finalize` become `needs_regeneration`, and `resume_stage = composition`.\ndocs/domain-model.md:170:   - Result: open on `resume_stage = finalize`, but still allow explicit navigation back to earlier stages for edits.\ndocs/domain-model.md:185:- The backend service layer, not the frontend, decides whether a requested stage transition is valid for the current session snapshot.\ndocs/realtime-events.md:5:of event families, and explicit links back to the durable event log.\ndocs/realtime-events.md:8:[docs/realtime-events.schema.json](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/realtime-events.schema.json).\ndocs/realtime-events.md:14:- Every live event belongs to exactly one story session.\ndocs/realtime-events.md:16:- Durable feed events carry `sequence_number` and `event_log_entry_id` so the\ndocs/realtime-events.md:17:  client can replay or deduplicate them.\ndocs/realtime-events.md:19:  forcing every partial token into the append-only event log.\ndocs/realtime-events.md:20:- Clients may optimistically render local actions, but server-emitted events stay\ndocs/realtime-events.md:22:  back to confirmed server events.\ndocs/realtime-events.md:27:One workspace tab opens one live connection and sends a session subscription\ndocs/realtime-events.md:52:  \"replay_strategy\": \"delta\",\ndocs/realtime-events.md:53:  \"replay_from_sequence_number\": 42,\ndocs/realtime-events.md:66:  events.\ndocs/realtime-events.md:71:- `last_sequence_number` is the last durable event the client has already\ndocs/realtime-events.md:72:  applied. The server uses it to decide whether replay can be a cheap delta or\ndocs/realtime-events.md:73:  whether the tab should rehydrate from the session snapshot endpoint.\ndocs/realtime-events.md:77:Every session event shares the same outer shape:\ndocs/realtime-events.md:82:  \"event_id\": \"rt-88\",\ndocs/realtime-events.md:94:  \"replayable\": true,\ndocs/realtime-events.md:96:  \"event_log_entry_id\": \"event-log-48\",\ndocs/realtime-events.md:103:- `event_id`: unique realtime-delivery identifier.\ndocs/realtime-events.md:104:- `type`: one of the event families below.\ndocs/realtime-events.md:106:- `actor`: who caused the change, reusing the durable event-log actor model.\ndocs/realtime-events.md:110:- `delivery`: `live` for freshly emitted events, `replay` for durable catch-up\ndocs/realtime-events.md:112:- `replayable`: `true` for events backed by the event log, `false` for ephemeral\ndocs/realtime-events.md:114:- `sequence_number` and `event_log_entry_id`: required on replayable events,\ndocs/realtime-events.md:127:| `error.notification` | yes | User-visible session or job error that should survive replay. |\ndocs/realtime-events.md:140:durable preview in the event log.\ndocs/realtime-events.md:152:- `resume_stage`\ndocs/realtime-events.md:171:This event exists so the UI and chat history stay coherent after direct clicks,\ndocs/realtime-events.md:195:This one event family leaves room for prompt 62 requirements:\ndocs/realtime-events.md:201:These events are intentionally ephemeral. Reconnect behavior should rebuild the\ndocs/realtime-events.md:202:accepted story state from durable composition records and then resume streaming\ndocs/realtime-events.md:207:This event is the replayable progress checkpoint for both composition and audio.\ndocs/realtime-events.md:275:should still be present after refresh or replay. Connection-level transport\ndocs/realtime-events.md:281:The event log remains the source of truth for replayable session history. The\ndocs/realtime-events.md:286:- Replayable live events should correspond 1:1 to durable `event_log_entries`\ndocs/realtime-events.md:287:  and copy over the same `sequence_number` and `event_log_entry_id`.\ndocs/realtime-events.md:288:- `delivery: \"replay\"` means the server is replaying already-persisted events\ndocs/realtime-events.md:291:  event log and should not be relied on for recovery.\ndocs/realtime-events.md:292:- When a reconnect misses ephemeral chunks, the client should rehydrate from the\ndocs/realtime-events.md:293:  latest session snapshot and then continue applying future live events.\ndocs/realtime-events.md:294:- The session snapshot endpoint from prompt 38 is the fallback when replay alone\ndocs/realtime-events.md:295:  is not enough or the server returns `replay_strategy: \"hydrate\"` in the\ndocs/realtime-events.md:314:only w