{"color": "green", "emoji": "\ud83d\udcac", "event_type": "Agent Message", "message": "Implemented session hydration end to end. The backend now has a dedicated replay/hydration service, `GET /api/v1/sessions/{id}/hydrate`, snapshot support for `latest_composition_job` and `latest_audio_job`, and safe replay of stage/job e...", "raw_event": {"item": {"id": "item_149", "text": "Implemented session hydration end to end. The backend now has a dedicated replay/hydration service, `GET /api/v1/sessions/{id}/hydrate`, snapshot support for `latest_composition_job` and `latest_audio_job`, and safe replay of stage/job events on top of relational state so failed or active jobs restore honestly. The workspace route now loads from that single hydration payload and initializes chat/history from the same response instead of doing separate snapshot and history reads.\n\nVerification passed:\n- `pytest backend/tests/test_session_hydration_service.py backend/tests/test_session_api.py backend/tests/test_session_service.py backend/tests/test_conversation_memory_evals.py`\n- `pytest backend/tests -m 'not integration'` with `103 passed, 5 deselected`\n- `ruff check backend/app backend/tests`\n- `npm test -- --run SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx sessionRuntimeStore.test.ts sessionChatPane.test.tsx`\n- `npm run lint`\n- `npm run build`\n\nI committed the code as `feat(prompt-38): session replay and resume hydration`. The required reviewer summary was written last to [summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.yolopilot/runs/20260331T205548_storyteller_prompt_pack/38_session_replay_and_resume_hydration/summary.md). Browser screenshots were not captured; this change was data-hydration behavior rather than layout/styling, so verification stayed at backend plus React test/build level.", "type": "agent_message"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 576, "prompt_index": 39, "prompt_name": "38 \u2014 Session Replay and Resume Hydration", "prompt_total": 100}, "timest